    • Content

      /*

big ML table of best model fit for subj vs. obj prob

21/12/2012 Markus Schaffner

based on:
*OET do file
*By Phil Tian
*version 11.2

@author Markus Schaffner

*/

clear all
set more off

cd "/Users/mas/Dropbox/EXPERIMENTS/OET/material"

cap log close
log using "log/table4_bigML.smcl", replace smcl

use "dta/oetaug2010_pitstoplevel_v8.dta", clear

sort subjectid pitstopid


gen pse = psexpectation / 1000
gen female = 0
replace female = 1 if gender == 1

gen age2 = age*age

replace winpc = 2^-100 if winpc == 0
sum winpc


// clean up relevant var names
label var winpc "Objectiv prob."
label var pse "Subjective prob."



// data clean
// drop subjects with incomplete information
drop if subjectid == 505 | subjectid == 822 | subjectid == 653

// drop due to luckyans
drop if subjectid == 263 | subjectid == 714 | subjectid == 729

// replace risk as 5 for inconsistent (5 beeing the uniform random outcome, N=19)
replace risk = 5 if mi(risk)

// replace BMI with average (affects 404 and 723)
replace BMI = 22 if mi(BMI)



// LBW
program define OET_ML1
args lnf sigma gamma alpha
tempvar j
gen double `j'=`alpha'*winpc^`gamma'/((`alpha'*winpc^`gamma'+(1-winpc)^`gamma'))
quietly replace `lnf'=ln(normalden(($ML_y1-`j')/`sigma'))-ln(`sigma')
end
ml model lf OET_ML1 (sigma:pse=) (gamma1:) (alpha1:)
ml search
ml maximize, difficult
// ml graph
estimates store m1


// Wu and GOnzales
program define OET_ML2
args lnf sigma gamma alpha
tempvar j
gen double `j'=winpc^`gamma'/((winpc^`gamma'+(1-winpc)^`gamma')^`alpha')
quietly replace `lnf'=ln(normalden(($ML_y1-`j')/`sigma'))-ln(`sigma')
end
ml model lf OET_ML2 (sigma:pse=) (gamma2:) (alpha2:)
ml search
ml maximize, difficult
// ml graph
estimates store m2


// Compund Invariant Prelect(1998) 
program define OET_ML3
args lnf sigma alpha beta gamma
tempvar j
gen double `j'=`gamma'*exp(-`beta'*(-ln(winpc))^`alpha')
quietly replace `lnf'=ln(normalden(($ML_y1-`j')/`sigma'))-ln(`sigma')
end
ml model lf OET_ML3 (sigma:pse=) (alpha3:) (beta3:) (gamma3:)
// ml check
ml search
ml maximize, difficult
// ml graph
estimates store m3


// Conditional Invariant Prelect(1998) 
program define OET_ML4
args lnf sigma eta beta gamma
tempvar j
gen double `j'=`gamma'*exp(-`beta'*(1-winpc^`eta')/`eta')
quietly replace `lnf'=ln(normalden(($ML_y1-`j')/`sigma'))-ln(`sigma')
end
ml model lf OET_ML4 (sigma:pse=) (eta4:) (beta4:) (gamma4:)
// ml check
ml search
ml maximize, difficult
// ml graph
estimates store m4



// using model4result.tex
estout m1 m2 m3 m4 using "tables/table4_bigML.tex", style(tex) replace ///
   mlabels(,nodepvars notitle none) eqlabels(, none) ///
   cells( b(fmt(%9.3fc)) se(fmt(%9.3fc) par) ) ///
   collabels(none) ///
   stats(N ll, fmt( %9.0f %9.3f) labels("\$N$" "\$ll$")) ///
   varlabels( sigma:_cons "\$\sigma$"  gamma1:_cons "\$\gamma_{LBW}$" alpha1:_cons "\$\alpha_{LBW}$" gamma2:_cons "\$\gamma_{WG}$" alpha2:_cons "\$\alpha_{WG}$" alpha3:_cons "\$\alpha_{Pcomp}$" beta3:_cons "\$\beta_{Pcomp}$"  gamma3:_cons "\$\gamma_{Pcomp}$" beta4:_cons "\$\beta_{Pcond}$" gamma4:_cons "\$\gamma_{Pcond}$" eta4:_cons "\$\eta_{Pcond}$" ) ///
   prefoot("\hline") ///
   starlevels(* 0.10 ** 0.05 *** 0.01)

log close

// EOF
